%N A394194 Number of fixed polyantelopes with n cells.
%C A394194 An antelope is a (3,4)-leaper. A polyantelope is a set of squares in the 2-dimensional grid, connected by antelope leaps. As usual, fixed means that we only identify forms that are translations of each other; for one-sided forms (A394195), translations and rotations are identified; for free forms (A394196), translations, rotations, and reflections are identified.
%C A394194 a(14) was found by _John Mason_.
%H A394194 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fairy_chess_piece">Fairy chess piece</a>.
%F A394194 a(n) = A151830(n) for 1 <= n <= 13. (See formula in A393390.)
%Y A394194 Row 5 of A393390.
%Y A394194 Cf. A030444 (polyknights), A093877 (polyzebras), A151830, A393836 (polygiraffes), A394195 (one-sided), A394196 (free), A394197.
